Installation:

    $ git clone git@github.com:vlasar/vim-web-dev.git ~/.vim
    $ git clone https://github.com/gmarik/vundle.git ~/.vim/bundle/vundle

Create symlinks:

    $ ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc

In vim run :BundleInstall to install the plugins.

Setting up snippets:
Change directory to '~/.vim/bundle/snipmate-snippets' and run: $ rake deploy_local

Installing Command-T:
vim must be compiled with ruby support and the Command-T plugin must be compiled against the same version of Ruby as was vim.
Change directory to '~/.vim/bundle/Command-T/ruby/command-t' and run: $ ruby extconf.rb && make

The majority of the .vimrc code taken from https://github.com/jelera
